CATEGORIES:Cultural
CATEGORIES:Medium Size
CATEGORIES:Casual/ Relaxed
DESCRIPTION:The Department of Art & Design presents the Spring 2026 Art Fo
 rum series. Art Forum is a speaker series featuring artists\, designers\,
  art historians\, curators\, and art critics from around the world presen
 ting their work and ideas in an open forum. \n \nThe next speaker in this
  engaging series is Athena LaTocha\, an artist whose works on paper explo
 re the relationship between human made and natural environments. She will
  discuss her practice and share insights into her latest work.\n \nAthena
  LaTocha is an artist whose works on paper explore the relationship betwe
 en human-made and natural worlds\, in the wake of Earthworks artists from
  the 1960s and 1970s. The artist incorporates materials such as ink\, lea
 d\, soils and wood\, looking at mark-marking and displacement of material
 s made by industrial equipment and natural events. Her works are informed
  by her upbringing in the wilderness of Alaska. LaTocha’s process is abou
 t being immersed in these environments\, while responding to the storied 
 and\, at times\, traumatic histories that are rooted in place.\n \nThis s
 peaker series is free and open to the public.\n \n📅 Art Forum\nMonday\, 
 3/23/26  5:20pm-7pm\nCalcia Hall\, Room 140\n\nHosted by: Art and Design\
 n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.c
 om/engage/event/12343653
DTEND:20260323T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260322T024908Z
DTSTART:20260323T212000Z
GEO:40.859750;-74.199750
LOCATION:Calcia 140\, Calcia Hall
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Art Forum Speaker Series featuring Athena LaTocha
UID:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12343653
URL:https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12343653
X-HOSTS:Art and Design
END:VEVENT
