SUMMARY:Writing: Method and Motivation
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to register.\n\nA 
 workshop for anyone who wants to write\, or wants to infuse their existing 
 writing practice with new energy. In each class\, we'll consider one 
 element of fiction or creative non-fiction\, such as point of view\, 
 narrative voice\, and what makes a piece of writing riveting\, or boring. 
 Students can expect in-class writing prompts\, reading aloud\, and optional 
 homework. Positive encouragement\, rather than formal critiques\,  will be 
 featured\, and inspiration and organization for writers will be discussed. 
 Students should bring whatever they use to write to each class.\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Conference Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
UID:LibCal-10306-15798126
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15798126
