CATEGORIES:Academic/Educational
CATEGORIES:Meeting
DESCRIPTION:Please join us for two exciting activities! First\, Ms. Jenny 
 Pollack\, Education Director for the Yogi Berra Museum & Learning Center 
 will speak about employment opportunities to be a STEM and Sports educato
 r to K-12 students who visit the Museum & Learning Center on class trips 
 throughout the academic year. This is a terrific opportunity for CSAM sci
 ence students who want to get experience teaching science to children - a
 nd it is right here on campus! The second activity will be a social 'buil
 d your own button' activity -- leave with a custom button of your own des
 ign for your backpack!\n \nThe CSAM Science Teaching Program holds biweek
 ly meetings that are open\, welcoming\, and inclusive! Any student curiou
 s about science teaching is invited to join us. Each meeting highlights a
  theme related to science education\, from classroom strategies to career
  pathways\, and offers students opportunities to connect with mentors\, e
 xplore internships\, and gain real-world experience working with teachers
  and children. Students are encouraged to bring a guest who may also be i
 nterested in exploring science teaching.\nThese gatherings help us build 
 a strong community of support\, where students encourage one another\, sh
 are experiences\, and access valuable opportunities such as scholarships\
 , paid internships\, and mentoring from advanced peers and in-service sci
 ence teachers. Whether you are just beginning to explore the idea of teac
 hing or already on the path toward certification\, these meetings are a p
 lace to grow\, learn\, and belong.\n\nHosted by: College of Science and M
 athematics (CSAM)\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://mont
 clair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/11712552
DTEND:20260325T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260322T024908Z
DTSTART:20260325T180000Z
LOCATION:SCHM 329 (CSAM Innovation and Design Lab)
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:CSAM Science Teaching Program - Program Meeting
