DESCRIPTION:NEW DATE FOR SESSIONS! \nAs immigration policies develop\, it 
 is best to stay educated. Know your rights and responsibilities!\nJoin th
 e New Jersey Consortium for Immigrant Children for a webinar on key legal
  and policy issues impacting the Montclair community. Information will be
  provided on immigration statuses\, policy updates\, legal protections\, 
 judicial vs. administrative orders\, and understanding your rights if enc
 ountering law enforcement. Sessions are open for students\, family\, facu
 lty\, and staff in both English and Spanish. \nThe New Jersey Consortium 
 for Immigrant Children (NJCIC) is a state-wide legal and policy advocacy 
 and education organization specializing in youth immigration. They provid
 e objective legal resources\, aid\, and advice on immigration rights.\n \
 nStudent & Family English Session: March 25\, 2:00-3:15: https://us06web.
 zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_FxYlh_kDRkCYCoOhfmEKyA#/registration\nStudent
  & Family Spanish Session: April 9\, 5:30-6:45: https://us06web.zoom.us/j
 /82724283081?pwd=KzAjQw24vxqmzbURBXGmbBLV3V60m3.1\n\nHosted by: College f
 or Education and Engaged Learning\, Government Relations and Community Af
 fairs \, Office of Student Belonging\, Office for Hispanic Initiatives\, 
 Office of Community Engagement and Partnerships\, The Office for Experien
 tial Education and Career Connections\n\nOnline Location: https://us06web
 .zoom.us/webinar/register/WN_FxYlh_kDRkCYCoOhfmEKyA#/registration\n\nAddi
 tional Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/enga
 ge/event/12262773
DTEND:20260325T191500Z
DTSTAMP:20260322T024908Z
DTSTART:20260325T180000Z
LOCATION:Online
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Understanding Rights and Responsibilities— Immigration Policy
