SUMMARY:CANCELED: MILL @ MPL: Senior Fridays
DESCRIPTION:A day of activities for Seniors - every Friday!\n\n \n\nJoin us 
 on Fridays for a day full of events for Seniors with the MILL @ MPL! All 
 events are free and open to the public. Registration is recommended unless 
 otherwise noted.\n\nFollow this link to register for MILL classes.\n\nFor 
 questions about MILL classes please call 973-744-3278.\n\nMILL @ MPL is 
 made possible through a partnership between the MILL\, Montclair Public 
 Library and Partners for Health.\n\nMarch 27 MILL @ MPL Senior Fridays 
 Schedule of Events:\n\n10:30 a.m. - 11:15 a.m.: Chair Yoga 
 (Auditorium)\n11:30 a.m. - 12:30 p.m.: Where Am I Going? Housing Options 
 for Seniors (Auditorium)\n11:30 a.m. - 12:30 p.m.: Bereavement Group (Tower 
 Room)\n12:30 p.m. - 1:30 p.m.: Lunch provided by Toni's Kitchen 
 (Auditorium)\n1:30 p.m. - 3:30 p.m.: Book and Manuscript Illustration with 
 Maggie Rothman (Auditorium\, Hybrid)\n\nPhotographs may be taken during our 
 programs and events for promotional purposes such as social media and 
 e-newsletters. If you do not wish to have your photograph taken please let 
 us know before the event.\n\nTo stay informed\, sign up for one or all of 
 our eNewsletters\, click here.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult Services, Fitness, Health & Wellness, Lectures / History & Culture
