UID:10003877-1774789200-1774796400@www.unioncong.org
SUMMARY:Lenape Way Walks with Creation Justice Team (Offsite)
DESCRIPTION:On Sunday\, March 29th\, we will hike some familiar and lesser-known parts of the Lenape Trail. It is not as old\, long\, well-known or as crowded as the Camino de Santiago in Spain\, but parts of the trail are in Montclair and Bloomfield: Mills Reservation\, the Iris Gardens\, Tuers Park\, Brookdale Park and Clark’s Pond. Join us on our walk together as we connect to ourselves\, each other\, and to the Lenape people indigenous to this land. This walk will be family-friendly.
URL:https://www.unioncong.org/event/lenape-way-walks-with-creation-justice-team-offsite-3/
LOCATION:Off Site
CATEGORIES:All Church Events,All Events,Featured Events,Justice & Community Engagement
ORGANIZER;CN="Creation Justice":MAILTO:contact@unioncong.org
END:VEVENT
