SUMMARY:All Our Voices: Hindi Storytime (Ages 2-6)
DESCRIPTION:Families are invited to enjoy a bilingual Hindi Storytime with 
 storyteller Kruti Suba Coneti as she reads fun Children's books. Kruti is a 
 licensed ESL educator\, founder and owner of InkPageImagination’s The 
 Magic Reading Room\, and a passionate advocate for multilingual\, 
 multicultural literacy. As a mother raising two multilingual readers and 
 first-generation Americans\, she brings both personal insight and 
 professional expertise to everything she does. \n\nNo registration 
 required.\n\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Storytime Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Programs, Language, Storytime
UID:LibCal-10306-16375401
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16375401
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Libcal Bccls 10306": "https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16395205"}
X-SOURCE-ID:libcal_bccls_10306
X-SOURCE:Libcal Bccls 10306
DTSTART:20260329T203000Z
DTEND:20260329T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260329T000000Z
SUMMARY:The Penny Power Project: Financial Literacy for Kids (Grades 2-5)
DESCRIPTION:The Penny Power Project aims to teach the students about the 
 essentials of financial literacy. Throughout the three-week course\, the 
 program will cover various topics like budgeting\, saving\, investing\, 
 loans\, the history of money\, the functions of money\, exchange rates\, 
 and how interest works. Additionally\, the course will also instruct 
 students on how they can apply what they’ve learned to their lives 
 through fun activities and videos.\n\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Storytime Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Programs
UID:LibCal-10306-16395205
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16395205
END:VEVENT
