SUMMARY:Mah Jongg: Open Play
DESCRIPTION:PLEASE NOTE: You must sign up for EACH INDIVIDUAL SESSION. 
 Signing up for one session does not register you for any following classes. 
 Open Play is open on a first come\, first served basis. \n\nOpen Play is 
 the perfect setting for players who know the basics and want to enjoy 
 friendly games\, practice their skills\, and build confidence at the table. 
 We'll bring the tiles\, and all the accessories.  You bring your 2025 
 National Mah Jongg League card and your love of the game! The focus is on 
 learning to play independently\, building camaraderie\, and having fun. 
 Come meet fellow Mah Jongg enthusiasts\, sharpen your strategies\, and 
 enjoy the lively spirit of the game!\n\nStudents must know the basics of 
 mah jongg.  If you're new to the game\, or don't feel comfortable sitting 
 at a table and playing with others at a similar level\, please register for 
 a Beginner class by clicking here. Skip dates are Feb. 9th and 16th.\n\n 
 \n\nPLEASE NOTE:\n\n\n	Students should have taken Beginner Mah Jongg or 
 have equivalent knowledge and experience. \n\n\nStudents should bring the 
 2025 National Mah Jongg League card to Open Play.\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Cafe Area\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
