SUMMARY:Book a Reading Specialist (parents/educators of grades PreK-12)
DESCRIPTION:\n\nDid you know Montclair Public Library Youth Services has a 
 full-time Reading Specialist?\n\nGina Chung Fortt has 14 years of 
 experience in the Elementary grades as a classroom teacher and pull-out 
 Reading Specialist. Gina is super passionate about supporting struggling 
 readers and empowering parents and caregivers to guide their child(ren)'s 
 literacy journey.\n\nPlease sign up for a 30-minute consultation with our 
 Youth Services Reading Specialist. Some topics may include:\n\n\n	How to 
 support your child's reading at home\n	Review your child's current reading 
 assessment (please bring copies\, if possible)\n	Learn what resources we 
 have at the library to check out for your developing or struggling 
 reader\n	Other areas of concern or curiosity regarding your child's 
 literacy development\n\n\nSign up HERE for a slot!\n\nAdults only. 
 Registration is required.\n\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Children's Floor\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Children's Programs, Reading Specialist
UID:LibCal-10306-16373063
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/16373063
END:VEVENT
