DESCRIPTION:Ashley Hall-Tighe MasterclassBeyond the Instrument: Building M
 ental Resilience and Finding Joy in Your Creative Life\nIn this interacti
 ve workshop\, life coach and professional musician Ashley Hall-Tighe guid
 es participants through practical strategies for navigating performance a
 nxiety\, perfectionism\, and the ever-present inner critic. Through refle
 ction and discussion\, musicians will learn tools to cultivate mental res
 ilience\, quiet negative self-talk\, and reconnect with the values and mo
 ments of joy that first inspired their creative journey.\nAshley Hall-Tig
 he is an internationally acclaimed trumpet soloist\, chamber musician\, a
 nd educator known for her warm tone\, expressive artistry\, and engaging 
 performances. Principal trumpet of the Cincinnati Chamber Orchestra since
  2008\, she recently toured worldwide with Canadian Brass. A dedicated te
 acher and Yamaha performing artist\, she serves on the faculty of the Uni
 versity of Cincinnati College-Conservatory of Music.\nAll are welcome. Re
 servations are not necessary.\n\nHosted by: The College of the Arts\n\nAd
 ditional Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/en
 gage/event/12348201
DTEND:20260401T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260322T024908Z
DTSTART:20260401T190000Z
GEO:40.858310;-74.199450
