X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup North Jersey Bowling Soccer Volleyball": "https://www.meetup.com/north-jersey-bowling-soccer-volleyball/events/313471493/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_north_jersey_bowling_soccer_volleyball
X-SOURCE:Meetup: NJ Bowling, Volleyball, Tennis & More
UID:event_313471493@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260322T025245Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260403T213000
SUMMARY:Bowling Night - North Jersey
DESCRIPTION:North Jersey Bowling\, Volleyball\, Tennis And More (BVT)\nThi
 s is an event for casual bowling at Montvale Lanes\, 14 W. Grand Ave. All 
 are welcome for **two games\, food and drinks**\, and any post- or pre-gam
 e hang out. Show up anytime! Questions or comments? You can message Andy M
 ilone on Meetup\, or call/text him at **201-234-9609**.\n\n\\*\\*\\* Befor
 e bowling\, we might stop by the Pizza Parlour\, 6 S. Kinderkamack Road in
  Montvale\, for a few slices at 6:15 p.m. First\, post a comment on the ev
 ent page to gauge interest. **After bowling\, we'll definitely be heading 
 to Davey's Irish Pub & Restaurant\, 5 Park St. in Montvale\, or The Ridge 
 Diner\, 125 Kinderkamack Road in Park Ridge\, at 10 p.m. for some food and
 /or drinks up until midnight.**\\*\\*\\*\n\nAbout the group: We're not pro
 fessionals and we're not in a league. In fact\, we're a group of people wh
 o probably each won't score more than 100 points and will land more than o
 ur fair share of gutter balls. There's no pressure at all!!!! We're not he
 re to analyze your form or technique.\n\nMore event details: You pay for y
 our own games\, food and drinks. Please bring cash. The alley does not acc
 ept card. But there is an ATM on site. The **cost per player is $18 for tw
 o games** and bowling shoes. If you have your own shoes\, the cost is $12.
  Please try to bring exact change since Andy will have a limited amount of
  cash. If you bring a $20 bill and Andy doesn't have change\, any remainde
 r would just go toward the bowling alley tip.\n\nFood and drinks (alcoholi
 c and non-alcoholic) are available on site\, plus tables and an alley bar 
 to hang at during the event. There is a dart board and a few arcade games\
 , as well.\n\n**What do you do when you get there?** First\, find the grou
 p inside around the front desk. Look for a growing group of people! Call o
 r text Andy Milone at 201-234-9609 if you can't find us. Pay Andy before g
 etting bowling shoes. **\\*NEW\\*** He'll give you a name tag or wrist ban
 d. **\\*NEW\\***\n\n**Please know that it is possible we have to wait 20-4
 0 minutes until lane(s) free up. (He is thinking about changes to possibly
  address this too).** It's certainly possible that we may have to relocate
  or cancel that night if there's a long wait list upon arrival. Please kee
 p that in mind if traveling from far away!\n\nFor those who don't have car
 s or are looking to avoid driving\, the Montvale Train Station is only lik
 e a five-minute walk from the bowling alley and can be reached via the Pas
 cack Valley Line. Last train leaves at 12:20 a.m. and heads toward Hoboken
 . (https://gmtma.org/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/rail_system_map.jpg)\n\nMa
 ny thanks to Taylor\, one of our group participants\, for recommending Mon
 tvale Lanes! You can learn more at: www.montvalelanes.com.\n\nHope you'll 
 join us for our 22nd bowling event\, or consider attending one of our voll
 eyball\, ping pong\, skating or other activities -> www.meetup.com/north-j
 ersey-bowling-soccer-volleyball
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/north-jersey-bowling-soccer-volleybal
 l/events/313471493/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260222T053402Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260222T053402Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
