SUMMARY:Friday Night Baseball Watch Party - North Jersey
DESCRIPTION:North Jersey Bowling\, Volleyball\, Tennis And More (BVT)\nCom
 e join the group to celebrate the third weekend of baseball at The Shepher
 d & The Knucklehead of Hoboken\, 1313 Willow Ave.\n\nNew York Mets and Yan
 kees games start at 7:10 p.m.\n\nOf course\, join us at any time. All you 
 gotta do is show up and have a good time hanging with familiar faces and m
 eeting new ones. It's totally optional to wear your favorite baseball gear
  or consume a few adult beverages.\n\nPlease be smart about travel. The tr
 ain station is not far away and runs late. Parking can be a challenge\, bu
 t there is street parking (where residential permit is not required) and s
 everal paid public parking garages\, including at 112 River St. and 1330 W
 illow Ave. Feel free to comment below if interested in carpooling or have 
 questions about travel options.\n\nQuestions? Suggestions? Concerns? You c
 an reach out to Andy Milone at 201-234-9609 (call/text)\, or by message ov
 er Meetup or Whatsapp.\n\nHope you'll consider attending one of our bowlin
 g\, volleyball\, table tennis\, skating or other activities -> [www.meetup
 .com/north-jersey-bowling-soccer-volleyball](https://www.meetup.com/north-
 jersey-bowling-soccer-volleyball)
