SUMMARY:Midday MeetUp - Jews and Baseball\, A Love Affair
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260414T114500
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260414T133000
DTSTAMP:20260318T050315Z
UID:TU2005886228
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20260414T114500
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20251211T205214Z
DESCRIPTION:**Midday MeetUp - Jews and Baseball\, A Love Affair**  \n  \nA
  monthly gathering to make connections and learn together.  \n11:45am Cate
 red Lunch (free)  \n12:30pm Featured Program   \n  \nJoin baseball histori
 an Sam Bernstein for a lively survey of Jewish involvement in America’s 
 National Pastime.  \n  \nCost:** FREE or Suggested Donation of $10 per per
 son to offset costs. (Bill My Account is only open to Shomrei Members)  \n
   \n**RSVP:** Required so we know how much food to buy.  \nhttps://shomrei
 .easyshul.com/events/6967e303368f110026c0c410  \n  \n**\\***Members &amp\;
  PreSchool Families should use their fob to access the building.  \n  \n**
 About the Program**  \nUsing audio and video\, *Jews and Baseball* explore
 s the origins of the game and the impact Jewish players\, owners\, and inn
 ovators have had on its evolution. The program highlights figures such as 
 Hank Greenberg\, Sandy Koufax\, Barney Dreyfuss\, Bud Selig\, Lou Boudreau
 \, Marvin Miller\, as well as the game's current Jewish stars. It also del
 ves into topics including antisemitism in the sport\, baseball’s growth 
 in Israel\, and the lore of the “Koufax Curse.”  \n  \n**About Sam Ber
 nstein**  \nSam Bernstein is a retired Social Worker who has published man
 y articles on baseball history. He received a BA in History from the Ameri
 can University and an MSW from Adelphi University. After a career serving 
 the Jewish community at JCCs and Jewish Family Service\, Sam worked for th
 e Elizabeth Public Schools and as an Instructor in Social Work for Rutgers
  University. He was raised in Malverne\, NY and moved to New Jersey with h
 is wife Maureen in 1999.  \n  \nFull_Season_Schedule_for_Midday_MeetUps: h
 ttps://shomrei.org/calendar/midday-meetup-calendar  \n  \n**Questions?** C
 ontact June Zimmerman\,   \nVP for Programming  \njzimmerman@shomrei.org  
 \n  \n\\#middaymeetup\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20260212T223313Z
LOCATION:Social Hall
TRANSP:OPAQUE
URL;VALUE=URI:https://teamup.com/kstx8swyw669kakgqa/events/2005886228
X-SOURCE:Congregation Shomrei Emunah
X-SOURCE-URL:https://shomrei.org/calendar/
X-TEAMUP-ROOM:Social Hall
END:VEVENT
