DESCRIPTION:Flute Masterclass with Jennifer Grim\nJennifer Grim\, professo
 r at the University of Miami\, will present a masterclass for the Cali fl
 ute studio\, where students will perform and receive individualized feedb
 ack.\nPraised by The New York Times as “a deft\, smooth flute soloist\,” 
 Jennifer Grim is a versatile performer whose work spans solo\, chamber\, 
 and orchestral stages worldwide.\nA member of the flute-percussion duo So
 lidaire and contemporary ensemble Flagelot\, she has collaborated with le
 ading groups including the Boston Chamber Music Society and Chamber Music
  Society of Lincoln Center. Her acclaimed album Through Broken Time refle
 cts her strong commitment to contemporary music.\nGrim is Professor and C
 hair of Instrumental Performance at the Frost School of Music\, Universit
 y of Miami\, and serves as President of the National Flute Association Bo
 ard.\n\nHosted by: The College of the Arts\n\nAdditional Information can 
 be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12353914
DTEND:20260417T010000Z
