CATEGORIES:Arts
DESCRIPTION:Tuba Masterclass with Willie Clark\nWillie Clark\, professor o
 f tuba at University of Maryland and former tuba with the United States A
 Ir Force Band will lead Cali brass students in a masterclass focusing on 
 the fundamentals of expressive brass playing across a landscape of genres
 .\nBio\nWillie Clark is a former member of the United States Air Force Ce
 remonial Brass and a founding member of the professional Disney tuba quar
 tet\, The Tubafours. An internationally active performer\, recording arti
 st\, and clinician\, he has toured extensively throughout the United Stat
 es\, South America\, Asia\, Australia\, and Europe\, performing with lead
 ing orchestras\, ensembles\, and popular artists. Clark currently serves 
 on the tuba faculty at the University of Maryland and Howard University\,
  and is widely respected for his engaging teaching and expressive approac
 h to brass performance.\n\nHosted by: The College of the Arts\n\nAddition
 al Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/e
 vent/12350899
