BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Ics Kstx8Swyw669Kakgqa 6478083 Ics": "https://teamup.com/kstx8swyw669kakgqa/events/2025222010"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ics_kstx8swyw669kakgqa_6478083_ics
SUMMARY:Here All Along: Sarah Hurwitz on Finding Judaism  
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T170000
DTSTAMP:20260318T050315Z
UID:TU2025222010
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/New_York:20260426T150000
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Events
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260115T234631Z
DESCRIPTION:**Seth Goodchild Memorial Lecture**  \nReception immediately f
 ollowing  \n  \nRSVP:   \n  \n**About the Program**  \nDuring the final ye
 ars of her tenure in the White House as First Lady Michelle Obama’s head
  speechwriter\, Sarah reconnected with Judaism and was astonished to disco
 ver thousands of years of wisdom from her ancestors about what it means to
  be human. She found beautiful rituals that honor the past and sanctify th
 e present\; wildly diverse conceptions of God\, none of which were a beard
 ed man in the sky\; and guidance on living an ethical life that set a much
  higher bar for honesty\, generosity\, and basic human decency than she ha
 d ever thought to set for herself. Sarah shares insights about how the wis
 dom of an ancient tradition can transform our lives today\, inspiring Jews
  to embrace and celebrate their heritage.   \n  \n**Free Babysitting Avail
 able**  \nEmail Aviva Arad\, aarad@shomrei.org  \n  \n**\\*Additional park
 ing is available next door at 73 &amp\; 77 Park Street.**  \n  \n**In Lovi
 ng Memory of Seth Goodchild**   \nSeth Goodchild was inspired by trips to 
 Israel to convert to Judaism at age 61. To honor his life and legacy\, his
  friends and family established a fund for Shomrei Emunah to continue and 
 spread his commitment to Judaism for the broader community.\n\n
LAST-MODIFIED:20260219T184433Z
TRANSP:OPAQUE
URL;VALUE=URI:https://teamup.com/kstx8swyw669kakgqa/events/2025222010
X-SOURCE:Congregation Shomrei Emunah
X-SOURCE-URL:https://shomrei.org/calendar/
END:VEVENT
