DESCRIPTION:**Midday Meetup - Jersey Tomato  \n  \nA monthly gathering to 
 make connections and learn together.  \n11:45am Catered Lunch (free)  \n12
 :30pm Featured Program   \n  \nFood historian\, Judith Krall-Russo\, will 
 talk about where the tomato originated and why it became one of New Jersey
 ’s favorite crops\, the history of the tomato industry in New Jersey\, a
 bout heirloom varieties\, modern hybrids and the folklore attached to toma
 toes.  \n  \n**Cost:** FREE or Suggested Donation of $10 per person to off
 set costs. (Bill My Account is only open to Shomrei Members)  \n  \n**RSVP
 :** Required so we know how much food to buy.  \nhttps://shomrei.easyshul.
 com/events/6967e4b6368f110026c0c460  \n  \n**\\***Members &amp\; PreSchool
  Families should use their fob to access the building.   \n  \nFull_Season
 _Schedule_for_Midday_MeetUps: https://shomrei.org/calendar/midday-meetup-c
 alendar  \n  \n**Questions?** Contact June Zimmerman\,   \nVP for Programm
 ing  \njzimmerman@shomrei.org  \n  \n\\#middaymeetup\n\n
