DESCRIPTION:Our Community Shavuot Tikkun is a long standing local traditio
 n. Members from Bnai Keshet\, Temple Sholom of West Essex\, Temple Ner Tam
 id\, and Congregation Shomrei Emunah will once again come together to stud
 y and discuss interesting Jewish topics late into the night. Each year one
  of our local community synagogues takes a turn as host. **The host this y
 ear is .**  \n  \n**Guest Scholar:**   \n  \n**Schedule**   \n5:30pm - You
 ng Families Program (please RSVP: https://www.bnaikeshet.org/bnaikeshet.or
 g/shavuot#family for this activity)  \n7:00pm - Pizza dinner for teens  \n
 7:30pm - Festival Maariv Evening Service and Oneg  \n9:00pm - Keynote Addr
 ess  \n10:00pm - Breakout Study Sessions 1  \n11:00pm - Breakout Study Ses
 sions 2   \n12:00am - Reading of the Ten Commandments  \n12:30am - Final T
 eaching from Dr Elsie Stern\n\n
